HEADWORD: broadbean
<hw>broadbean</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an Old World upright plant grown
esp. for its large flat edible seeds but also as fodder.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> broad bean, broad-bean plant, English bean, European
bean, field bean, Vicia faba.</syn>⟦br⟧
